## RUNs comparisons

# RUN1

# Synthetic log Welch t test

```{r}
t.test(x=ceREC_loop1000_run1 , y=REC_loop1000_run1, var.equal=FALSE, paired = FALSE, mu = 0)

```


# Synthetic log Wilcoxon test
```{r}
x <- read.csv(file="Loop1000/ceREC_loop1000_run1.csv", header=TRUE, sep = "," , "rt")
y <- read.csv(file="Loop1000/REC_loop1000_run1.csv", header=TRUE, sep = "," , "rt")
ceREC <- print(x)
REC <- print(y)
x <- as.numeric(ceREC$Diff_ms)
y <- as.numeric(REC$diff_ms)
wilcox.test( x, y , alternative = "two.sided", paired = FALSE, mu=0)


```
